1.title: The Squad is Back!
1.plot: The California All Stars are back in action. It's time to round up a new team with the same dream; win gold at the USASF World Cheerleading Championships. Newcomers are ready to roll with the big kids while some of the vets are doing what they can to stay on top.

2.title: Coming Home!
2.plot: Tryouts may be over but no one's spot is secure. Veteran Team Reckless member Hayley is hoping to spend her senior year on Cali Smoed but it seems a few returners have come to reclaim their spot on the mat.

3.title: All About That Base
3.plot: Returner Cami is back and ready to go for the gold while newcomer Coleman is hoping to be a part of the Brotherhood. Both of them have been flyers their entire cheer career but with so many spots already filled will one of them be grounded? The team heads to camp to find out who has what it takes.

4.title: Welcome to the Brotherhood
4.plot: The boys of Cali SMOED are ready to welcome Coleman to the family but will he be able to earn his keep at Cali Camp? The vets decided to step in and give the newcomers some helpful tips.

5.title: The Show Off
5.plot: Meet Sam. He's packed full of talent and ready to earn a spot with the brotherhood. The team works with their buddy coach Kyle to make sure they hit for the Cali Camp Show Off. With so many extra members on the team the pressure is on.

6.title: Reckless in Love
6.plot: Cali Team Reckless is back and ready to fight for the gold.

7.title: Mental Games
7.plot: The team is back from camp but with a few too many athletes. Everyone will be tested and cuts will be made.

8.title: He's Back!
8.plot: A blast from the past returns for the 200th episode of Cheerleaders. This Cali Smoed Alumni takes one of the new boys under his wing.

9.title: Fresh Meat
9.plot: Meet Amber. Coming all the way from Utah she is hoping to secure a spot on cali smoed. Five flyers are in place but with two more in the wings it's anyone's game.

10.title: Reckless Heartbreaker
10.plot: Today is the final day of assessments for Team Reckless, or as Orby likes to call it "Break The Heart Day". The team is about to get smaller, and with a few old members back in the gym it could be an intense and emotional day for everyone.

11.title: The Heat is On
11.plot: The routine is coming together but seems like a key member may be falling apart. An alternate is up for the challenge and steps up to a plate while another teammate begins to slack.

12.title: The Reckless Twins
12.plot: Reckless evaluations are over and your favorite fill now has an official spot on the team.

13.title: Love and Loss
13.plot: With Coleman leaving the team right before the showcase, the rest of the squad will have to adjust to make up for his absence on the floor. Meanwhile, love is in the air as a familiar face returns to the sidelines.

14.title: Center Flyer
14.plot: Marking the start of season, the athletes reminisce over all the memories they've shared. But its not all sunshine and flowers, Ari's injury has left her sidelined and as her replacement continues to excel she's worried about her position on the team.

15.title: The Young and the Reckless
15.plot: After weeks of training, both SMOED and Reckless are finally ready to hit the mat for the weekend's performances. There is no room for nervousness, only excitement and execution. Who will hit?

16.title: Jazzy's Back!
16.plot: Kira joins Robert at the dance studio to show him some support and learn some new moves to help her on the floor. Also, we have some familiar faces re-joining SMOED. Not only has Jazzy decided to return to the mat but a fourth boy has made his way back too.

17.title: Ride or Die!
17.plot: With SMOED's first big competition happening, the team is working hard to get the final pieces together. But with besties Ari and Cami dealing with potential injuries, things may soon fall apart before they begin.

18.title: Fire and Ice
18.plot: With the recent fires raging in California, The California All Stars have gotten together to donate to those affected by the tragedy.

19.title: Shook to the Ground
19.plot: It's make it or break it for Reckless and no one's spot is secure. With Chimmy getting bumped up to center flyer and teammates switching in and out, who will make it to the mat for the team's first competition?

20.title: Come to Jesus
20.plot: Cheer Alliance is around the corner and the pressure is on for SMOED to show the country's top competitors what they're made of. Will the team hit, or will they fall apart before they even make it to Louisville?

21.title: Just Married
21.plot: Guess who finally put a ring on it?. Eddie and Orby head down the aisle to say "I Do". Meanwhile, the team is doing all they can to secure a bid to the World Cheerleading Championships, but can the center group keep it together?

22.title: Life Without Cheer
22.plot: The time has come to say goodbye to two of our alumni. While Chimmy and Robert move on to the next chapter of their lives, two old faces are coming in to the rescue. Will they have what it takes to stay on the mat?

23.title: Amateur Hour
23.plot: Competition season is underway and Coach Eddie wants to step up the difficulty. Team Reckless is trying to work their new alternates into the full routine. Meanwhile, SMOED's center stunt begins to feel the pressure.

24.title: Something's Gotta Give
24.plot: Smoed is coming off of a big win, while Reckless still has a lot to prove this season. The cheer life might be stressful, but that doesn't mean the teammates can't stop to have some fun. Will Reckless come together and make Orby proud?

25.title: Ready for It
25.plot: Smoed is coming off of a big win, while Reckless still has a lot to prove this season. The cheer life might be stressful, but that doesn't mean the teammates can't stop to have some fun. Will Reckless come together and make Orby proud?

26.title: The Big Risk
26.plot: Sometimes things don't go according to plan, but when hardship hits, you have to adapt. Hailey may have fallen hard, but she has her team to build her back up. Will Reckless and Smoed be able to push through this competition and come back harder?

27.title: Work for Perfection
27.plot: It's NCA month and it's time to get down to business. After a rough showing at the CheerPros competition, the team needs to buckle down. With Eddie gone coach Kassidy plans to put them in their place.

28.title: Long Distance Love
28.plot: After a medical incident at the last competition for Team Reckless, Haylie's fate is left in Orby's hands. With a few familiar faces back on the team, it looks like Jade and Enrique's long distance love will come to a happy ending.

29.title: Love Yourself
29.plot: Mental health matters both in and out of practice. Kira's back as an alternate with the support of her team as Reckless and Smoed head into the last practice before NCA, but she's not the only familiar face back in the gym. With stunts falling on all sides, will the team be able able to hit when it counts?

30.title: Road to Dallas
30.plot: The team hits the mat for the final run before they head down the road to Dallas for NCA Nationals. Will a missed flight hold them down?

31.title: Get a Grip
31.plot: The California All Stars head to The Cheer Athletics facility in Plano Texas for one final push before they hit the mat at NCA nationals. Reckless can't seem to get a grip on their pyramid but can they get it together before their NCA debut?

32.title: Don't Be That Girl
32.plot: SMOED is back in the gym after a rough placing at NCA and they've got some work to do. Maliea's stunt group can't seem to hit. With all eyes on the flyers it's time for her group to pull it together in time for their UCA debut.

33.title: Cheerleading is Hard
33.plot: After a tough loss at The NCA National Championships, Orby is taking things pretty hard. He decides to bring in some reinforcements to make sure they take gold at The World Cheerleading Championships.

34.title: Pop, Lock and Drop
34.plot: After a rough NCA placing SMOED finally comes back to the gym with a big victory. But there's no time for games as it's hard to stay on top when the flyers are coming down.

35.title: Another One Bites the Dust
35.plot: It wouldn't be Team Reckless without injuries. One member literally catches a break and is out for the season. Meanwhile, it's Worlds month and Eddie makes it known that no ones spot is safe. Will a familiar face claim a spot on the Worlds mat?

36.title: Blood, Sweat and Tears
36.plot: Worlds week is here but two members won't make the mat. After a miscount, coach Orby has to make the tough decision of removing someone from TeamRECKLESS. Meanwhile, the final straw has broken for a member of Cali SMOED.

37.title: Smeckless Showcase 2018
37.plot: SMOED and Reckless host their annual showcase for friends and family at the gym before traveling to Florida to compete at Worlds. But, with all the hard work the teams are putting in, injuries are bound to happen. The emotions rise with SMOED seniors as they end their run on the team with a bang.

38.title: Gatorland
38.plot: Team SMOED and team Reckless are off to Worlds. But will Eddie and Orby make the flight? Seems unlikely. Once they've arrived the team goes to Gatorland for some team bonding and fun. They find a good luck charm but will it help them win Worlds?.

39.title: Hit or Miss
39.plot: The final countdown is here as both teams head to Top Gun for their last practice together. With Santwons injury, Orby is left to make a decision to make for the team. Meanwhile SMOED has to try and try again in order to go into Day 1 confident.

40.title: Worlds 2018 Day 1
40.plot: It's Day 1 of the USASF World Cheerleading Championships and the California All Stars are ready to go.

41.title: Worlds 2018 Day 2
41.plot: Through blood, sweat, and tears the California All Stars have made it to day two of the USASF World Cheerleading Championships, and they have one last chance to impress the judges and take home the title after their rocky performances on day one. This is their last full-out as a team this season, and everyone is already missing their SMAMILY.

23.title: Dallas, Pt. 3
23.plot: It's the final day at NCA's National Championship and it's once again SMOED versus their rival Brandon for the championship title. Can SMOED win NCA for a third year in a row, or will Brandon regain the title that was once theirs?

24.title: Back to Work
24.plot: The squad returns to the gym from Dallas after falling to 2nd place at NCA's National Championship. Lauren talks about her difficult time at NCA, while Eddie and Orby put the team back to work.

25.title: The Final Push
25.plot: It's the home stretch for Smoed because the World Championships are coming up quick. The team is competing one more time in San Diego to see how they look before Worlds.

26.title: San Diego Pt.1
26.plot: Worlds is just around the corner and SMOED has one more hurdle they have to overcome. The squad travels to San Diego for their last competition before hitting the Worlds stage and Eddie is looking for perfection.

27.title: San Diego Finals Pt.2
27.plot: With Coach Eddie unhappy after a troubling first day at the San Diego Competition, SMOED has to step it up and hit their routine. It's their last chance to show what they've got before hitting the World's stage.

1.title: Battle of the Boys
1.plot: SMOED is back to business in this brand new season of Cheerleaders. Coming off of their 2nd World Championship win, Eddie and Orby are ready to work the team harder than ever. Tryouts are starting and the competition is fierce for the 20 coveted spots. With only 4 positions available for the boys, Eddie is putting them through their paces. With Michaeleddie, Kyle and a SMOED veteran returning, will Robert make the cut? See the battle of the boys begin in the world premiere of AwesomenessTV's Cheerleaders Season 2.

5.title: The Show Must Go On
5.plot: Travis receives the results of his injury. Will it be serious enough for him to quit? If it is where does that leave the team to find a new boy with competition season just right around the corner. Cheerleaders are put to the test and the pressure is on to make sure that people are pulling their weight. Watch and see if they'll have to find a new boy on this episode of Cheerleaders.

6.title: Mental Block
6.plot: One of SMOED'S rookie athletes, Kelsey, is having a mental block. Being far away from home and her family and boyfriend is taking its toll and it's showing on the practice floor. With competition season around the corner, Eddie is not having it and either she shapes up or she gets shipped out. Can Kelsey keep up or is she too homesick to go on? Find out what happens in this week's episode of AwesomenessTV's Cheerleaders Season 2.

7.title: Our Fearless Leader
7.plot: One of SMOED'S rookie athletes, Kelsey, is having a mental block. Being far away from home and her family and boyfriend is taking its toll and it's showing on the practice floor. With competition season around the corner, Eddie is not having it and either she shapes up or she gets shipped out. Can Kelsey keep up or is she too homesick to go on? Find out what happens in this week's episode of AwesomenessTV's Cheerleaders Season 2.

8.title: The Value of Life
8.plot: The squad is about to compete in their first competition of the season, but before they do, the cameras take a step outside of the gym to look into a serious issue that hurts millions of kids around the world. Bullying is one of the country's biggest problems for teens and two of Smoed's athletes are being tormented at school. Find out how they are handling it and moving beyond it to keep focused and pull up for the first competition of the season GSSA.

9.title: Mind Over Matter
9.plot: Smoed is back to business to try and secure their spot competing at the World Championships. Eddie and Orby's rule is that if they don't get a full paid bid they don't go. In order to do that, they must compete for two days in San Jose where the bid is given to just two squads. Making matters worse, one of the veteran athletes is injured and shouldn't be competing. Who is it? Can the team push through and hit? Find out in this episode of AwesomenessTVs Cheerleaders Season 2.

10.title: The Curse
10.plot: SMOED is gearing up for the dreaded Palm Springs competition. Although they managed to pull together for a win in 2013, something unexpected happens every year. With Kassidy out and Malia back in 3 days before they compete, can Malia get back into the swing of things and help her team break the dreaded Palm Springs Curse? Watch and see in this week's episode of Cheerleaders Season 2.

11.title: SMOED vs the Curse
11.plot: Smoed is in Palm Springs for the Spirit Sports competition and there is one thing on everyone's mind: The Palm Springs Curse. Nerves are kicking in, as the team is about to compete in Day 1 of the competition. After last year's win the score is The Curse 2, SMOED 1. However, last year's routine wasn't perfect. Will Smoed finally be able to even the score and break the curse? Watch and see in this episode of Cheerleaders Season 2.

12.title: Farewell Jenee
12.plot: SMOED returns from Palm Springs to some unexpected news: they are loosing two of the veterans on the team. They are devastated by the loss, but the show must go on. They are less than two weeks away from competing at the largest all-star national cheerleading championship, NCA. Will they be able to overcome their emotions and pull together as a Smamily during this difficult time? Will they be ready for NCA as they scramble to find two new members? Watch and see in this week's episode of Cheerleaders Season 2.

13.title: Welcome to Dallas
13.plot: Smoed is in Dallas for the National Championships and the nerves are kicking in. This is the biggest competition of the season and it's Peyton's first performance with the team. After a disappointing 2nd place last year, can they redeem themselves and become National Champions?

14.title: Play Time!
14.plot: Before Smoed continues to prepare for their Worlds run, Michaeleddie takes the spotlight on a different kind of stage. Back in the gym, two of the squad's veterans get into a bit of trouble and Coach Eddie is not happy. With Worlds right around the corner, will the team focus? What else is Michaeleddie doing outside of Smoed? See what's going on in this week's episode of AwesomenessTV's Cheerleaders Season 2.

15.title: The World Championships
15.plot: It's time for the competition we have all been waiting for, Smoed is on their way to the World Championship of Cheerleading. Watch the squad begin their journey to sunny Orlando, Florida. After a rough performance at their showcase, how confident is the team feeling, going into competition? Watch all of this and more on this week's Cheerleaders.

1.title: Here We Go Again
1.plot: The Cheerleaders are back! Coming off of four world title victories, the team is back in the gym with Coach Eddie. They are trying to be the first team to win their fifth consecutive world championship title. Although winning is in the teams blood, it isn't always easy. Championships aren't won overnight, and as the team gets the season started, the handwork begins on day one at tryouts!

2.title: A Lot on the Line
2.plot: As the preseason gets underway, the cheerleaders must prove to Coach Eddie that they are tough enough to be on the team. The girls are fighting for 16 spots while the boys are fighting for 4. There are five incredible male athletes trying out for the squad, but with only four spots, who will end up on the Cali Smoed roster?

3.title: Same Team, Same Dream
3.plot: With cuts being made and injuries taking place, its time for the squad to focus on the goal at hand. It's the details that make the difference between a second place team and a world championship team. Coach Eddie is determined to drill this into the minds of the cheerleaders; unfortunately some athletes aren't getting the message.

4.title: SMOED We Want to Be
4.plot: The curse is back! With injuries happening and cheerleaders leaving the team for personal reasons, the members of Cali Smoed are heartbroken when they find out they won't be able to attend the Cali Showcase this year to exhibition the routine they have been working so hard on.

5.title: Cali Super Camp Part 2
5.plot: The new members of Cali Smoed are starting to find out from the veterans what it's like to be a part of the squad. It's the last day of camp and they are getting a crash course in what it takes to be on one of the most innovative teams. Will they be ready for their first performance as a team or will they drop their stunt? Eddie's rule at camp is simple, you don't drop your stunt at Cali Camp.

6.title: Curse of the 4th Boy
6.plot: Smoed returns from Cali Super Camp for their first official team practice. They are hit with some unexpected news when they find out that they are one man down. Will Eddie and Orby find a solution to this familiar problem? The Curse of the Fourth Boy strikes again.

7.title: School's in Session
7.plot: Summer is over and it's back to school for some of the members of Cali Smoed. While Angel is enjoying the home school life, Gabi is returning to public school after a 5-year hiatus. Will the culture shock be too much for her or will she enjoy what high school has to offer?

8.title: Homesick
8.plot: Some of the Smoes have given up a lot to train with one of cheerleading's most prolific teams. Gabi is going on her 3rd year away from home while Payton is leaving the nest for the first time. See what it's like for these to when it comes to being homesick.

9.title: A Complete Team
9.plot: After a long summer, Cali Smoed finally has a complete team. Newcomers Cody and Alyssa are excited to join the team, while alternate Jessica is being given the second chance of a lifetime. How will this effect the stunt groups that have been working so hard the past 3 months? How will the teams chemistry be, now that Smoed finally has a complete team?

10.title: Goodbye Gabi Butler
10.plot: After 2 seasons with Cali Smoed, a valuable team member decides it's time to leave. The loss comes after a summer of ups and downs for the squad. Who is it and how will Eddie handle the situation?

11.title: A Whole New Me
11.plot: It's time for one of Smoed's veterans to start a new chapter. Eddie always says, "it's hard getting into the center, but it's even harder to stay there." With a new do and position as center flyer, is Madi ready to take on the challenge of being center stage for one of the most popular squads in Cheerleading?

12.title: We Got Annie
12.plot: It's The Hard Knock Life for The California All-Stars SMOED. Watch as the team gets a chance to let loose while doing a fun routine inspired by the new Annie movie.

13.title: My Dream Team
13.plot: After making many sacrifices and putting in countless hours of work, two members of the team become unsure of their fate on Smoed. While one is struggling to uphold her new position, the other experiences something out of her control.

14.title: Happy Holidays
14.plot: It's time for the annual Cali SMOED holiday party. Every year Eddie and Orby host an elaborate dinner party full of holiday cheer for the team. But this year is extra special because Eddie and Orby host the party at their home. It's a wonderful time for the team to bond, getting to spend time together outside of the cheer gym.

15.title: #BRAYTON
15.plot: After giving up her spot on Cali SMOED last season, Payton Coon made the big move to California. She's been away from her family, friends, and boyfriend for months while living with a host family.

16.title: Show and Tell
16.plot: After moving halfway across the globe, a member of Cali Smoed decides to leave unexpectedly before the showcase. The team moral has taken a hit but...a fire has been lit in their eyes.

17.title: Brand New Day
17.plot: After a successful showcase, the team is ready to put the past behind them and get back in the gym. The time has finally come to learn their pyramid.

18.title: The Last Practice
18.plot: The addition of the new 4th boy puts another members spot in jeopardy. It's out with the new and in with the old as a veteran returns to help fill the spot.

19.title: JAMZ Time!
19.plot: Cali SMOED learned their dance routine less than a week ago. The squad arrives to their first competition and gets their music one hour prior to competing. The pressure is mounting as the new team prepares to hit the competition floor.

20.title: The Final Faerwelll
20.plot: All good things come to an end. We've laughed, cried and have been on a rollercoaster of emotions with Cali SMOED. In this 100th episode of Cheerleaders, we say goodbye to the squad by showcasing the moments that made us fall in love with the team during their 3-year journey.

1.title: We're Back!
1.plot: At California All Stars Smoed, cheerleaders come and go, but Coach Eddie Rios always finds a way to maintain his high standards of success. This year, he'll have to building a winning team from scratch without Coach Orby Orta. Meet the new look of Cali Smoed, as they gear up for a run at the five-peat on the season premier of Cheerleaders.

2.title: Knock On Wood
2.plot: This new group of cheerleaders is bonding like never before. But for Eddie, assessments are the first order of business and nobody is safe from cuts. With the addition of an extra boy and girl to the team, everyone is feeling the heat.

3.title: The All Around Athlete
3.plot: This week Eddie gives a lesson in what happens if you don't give him 100%, and it's not pretty. This new crop of cheerleaders are quick to find out that there's no room for excuses and stragglers will be left behind.

4.title: A Lot On The Line
4.plot: The new members of SMOED are starting to really bond and have some fun but the countdown is on for the boys as only 4 of them will secure a coveted spot on the team. When a new boy comes to the gym he shakes things up.

5.title: The New Girl
5.plot: Cali Smoed may have an abundance of boys and the search is on for girls to fill the roster. But having one more girl means needing one less boy.

6.title: Reality Check!
6.plot: Meet Michelle, one of the newer members of the Smamily. SMOED is a tough team to get on, but it's even harder to stay. The threat of cuts has been looming over the boys' heads for weeks, and the day has finally come for a member of the brotherhood to pack up and head home.

7.title: Same Team, Same Dream
7.plot: After a summer filled with uncertainty, the squad finds out that one of their members has decided to make the tough decision of leaving the team.

8.title: Reckless
8.plot: Eddie and Orby have coached cheerleading side by side for years. This season is a bit different because Orby is coaching the new Small Coed Level 6 Team, Reckless. With a few familiar faces on the team from Cali Smoed, they are in for a fun time.

9.title: Moving On Up
9.plot: The team returns from a back to school break to find out that Eddie has made a few roster changes. Although it's a shock to some of the team...the show must go on. Eddie moves up two people from Snipers in hopes that they can step up to the plate. But being on Cali Smoed isn't easy.

10.title: The Curse
10.plot: A string of injuries has gotten coach Eddie thinking that the team is cursed. With the California All Stars showcase coming up in just a few weeks some of the team members aren't so sure about their dream of being on the coveted Cali Smoed will come true.

11.title: A Fighting Team
11.plot: Being away from home can be rough. With the delay into the performance season, one member decides that it might not be worth it. With Jade home for surgery a new member joins the cheerleading team in hopes of earning a permanent spot. Will a language barrier have her lost in translation? Watch and see Cali Smoed work as a team to overcome their recent setbacks.

12.title: Falling into Place
12.plot: Madi has taken on a new position in cheerleading. Growing up on Cali SMOED with Eddie as a coach means being able to adapt to whatever is thrown your way.

13.title: Put to the Test
13.plot: It's that time of the season for the dreaded 5 full outs. Eddie may have decided to pull the team from the annual Cali Showcase but that doesn't mean the team is catching a break.

14.title: Running out of Time
14.plot: Eddie brings in some reinforcements to give a few finishing touches to the routine but first it's time to trim some of the fat. The coaches need to shorten the routine and add in elements before they can throw an official full out.

15.title: Let's Hear it For the Boys!
15.plot: Cali Smoed has been chosen to appear on the cover of the Worlds edition for Inside Cheerleading Magazine. It's time to get out of the gym and head out to the wilderness of Ojai to take team photos with J. Tori Photography.

16.title: Get Tough
16.plot: Cali Smoed is used to having Eddie drill them day in and day out. This practice he decides to bring in a strong female that can push the team to their limits. The teams first performance is just weeks away and they just learned a new pyramid.

18.title: Time To Go
18.plot: Sickness and injury have been plaguing the team's preseason flow, but now it's time to put the final pieces together, and really make a Cali SMOED statement.

19.title: Today is the Day
19.plot: It's competition time. With the team feeling pressure to preform, Eddie is making sure the team is staying loose, and keeping their spirits high before the event. While everyone is having a good time, it's no excuse for sloppy mistakes. Everyone will need to be 100% to maintain Cali SMOED's high level of excellence.

20.title: #Openyourheart
20.plot: The holiday spirit has arrived at California Allstars. Instead of having their annual Christmas dinner, Coach Eddie and Orby have a plan to give back to those who need it most. Both Team Reckless and Cali SMOED are taking time away from the mat to spread holiday joy around the community.

21.title: Officially Cali SMOED
21.plot: Here we go. Now that all the hard work during practice has been put in, it's time for the team to hit the floor. With the bar set high by their predecessors, can this squad surpass expectations, and become the first to hit a clean routine during their season opener?

22.title: My Dream Quinceañera
22.plot: After a great first performance at the GSSA So Cal Classic, it's time for the team to get back to the gym and amp up their routine. Upping the difficulty adds a bit of pressure to some of the team members. A fun birthday surprise might be just what the team needs to take the edge off.

23.title: Battle of the Best
23.plot: Cheerleaders is back and competition season is underway. Both Cali SMOED and Team Reckless are gunning after a bid to the cheerleading world championships, but with only one bid up for grabs there can be no mistakes.

24.title: Chasing the Bid
24.plot: It's Day 1 of the GSSA Cheerleading Championships in Los Angeles, CA. The pressure is on for both Cali SMOED and Team Reckless as they chase the bid to the World Cheerleading Championships.

25.title: Chasing the Bid Pt. 2
25.plot: It's Day 2 of the GSSA Cheerleading Championships in Los Angeles, CA. Cali SMOED and Team Reckless are in the warmup room doing all they can to make sure they hit zero on the score sheet. With only one full paid bid up for grabs it's time for the teams to pull together more now then ever.

26.title: Chasing the Bid Pt. 3
26.plot: Day Two of the competition is here, and it's time for Team Reckless and SMOED to step up and take the mat. There are four teams all going for the coveted paid bid to the World Championships.

27.title: Get Out!
27.plot: Cali SMOED is back from break, and ready to get to work. This is the first time in three years that the team hasn't received a paid bid from GSSA. Frustration is rising amongst Coach Eddie as he continues to make roster changes. The time for mistakes is over and everyone is replaceable.

28.title: SMOED Lock-In
28.plot: Goodbye's are never easy, especially when it comes to family. Fortunately enough, the SMOED family is always there for love and support, especially with the annual Lock-In fundraiser. Kids from all over the country get a chance to get to know the Cheerleaders by spending the night, and competing in fun games and challenges.

29.title: The Curse is Back!
29.plot: A call to an old teammate is a sure reminder that anything can happen in cheerleading. It seems as though the team is experiencing the palm springs curse before they event set foot at the competition. Without a bid the they need to do whatever they can to come together and stay positive.

30.title: The Lion's Den
30.plot: It looks like some members of Cali SMOED are really starting to feel the pressure. With NCA cheerleading nationals quickly approaching Eddie is laying down the law.

31.title: Keep It Moving
31.plot: The team is back from Dallas and have temporarily relocated to a new gym. The new space is different and could make it difficult to focus for the next few weeks of practice. With injuries, illness, and shaky partner stunts, the team is struggling, but they will have to make it work if they want to win the world championships.

32.title: Never Been Kissed
32.plot: Love is in the air for young Madi. However, things are not all rainbows and smiles in the practice room. With worlds just a month away, the team isn't bringing the fire. Stunts aren't hitting and veteran's aren't stepping up.

33.title: Nobody Likes to Lose
33.plot: This is the last practice before the squad leaves for Champions League. Last year they got second in their division so this season they are going for the gold. However, the team isn't practicing like champions. With only one practice left before they leave, it's now or never for Cali Smoed.

34.title: Hey Guys, it's Champions League!
34.plot: It's time to head to head off to Champions League, but first Coach Eddie calls in the team for a special practice featuring Meg Deangelis from "Hey Guys, it's Meg!" Although it's a nice change of pace, Washington, D.C. awaits for Cali Smoed to try and take back their first place title in the coed division.

35.title: Dress to Impress
35.plot: The team is off to the Champions League Prom dressed to the nines but they can't forget it's time to work. The California All Stars are putting in work for the practice round to reclaim and defend their titles.

36.title: Battle of the Best!
36.plot: It's time for The California All Stars to hit the floor at champions league but there can only be one coed Grand Champion.

37.title: It's Party Time!
37.plot: Cali is SMOED is back in the gym and putting in work for their final competition before the World Cheerleading Championships. Eddie brings back Kenny Feeley to help reinforce the basics and maybe even put a smile on the kids faces.

38.title: The Cali Finale Pt. I
38.plot: It's time for the GSSA Cali Finale and Cali SMOED has come to secure a win before they head off to Orlando.

39.title: The Cali Finale Pt. II
39.plot: The end of the season is near and Cali SMOED has one last chance to prove that they are a team that can HIT both days before heading to the World Cheerleading Championships.

40.title: The Smeckless
40.plot: The team is back from Cali Finale and it's time for SMOED and Reckless to come together in their final send off before World Cheerleading Championships. It's one of the last times that everyone on the team will be together and, despite some technical difficulties, they're ready to hit the mat.

41.title: Worlds 2016 Part 1
41.plot: After months of blood, sweat and tears, Cali SMOED hops on a plane to Orlando, Florida for the World Cheerleading Championships. With minutes left before takeoff the team quickly realizes that not everyone has made it onto the plane.

42.title: Worlds 2016 Part 2
42.plot: The cheerleaders are in Orlando and it's finally time for Day 1 of the World Cheerleading Championships. The team is looking good at practice, but they have to make sure that they stay just as confident when they're on the competition mat.

43.title: Worlds 2016 Part 3
43.plot: After two unexpected stunt falls during their Day 1 performance, Cali SMOED just barely makes it into the final Top 10. The team heads over to the Top Gun Cheerleading facility to have one final practice before the most important day of the year.

44.title: Worlds 2016 Part 4
44.plot: It all comes down to this. It's Day 2 at the World Cheerleading Championships and the team is going for the unheard of, a 5-peat. The team comes together to realize that they all have to be in it to win it.

1.title: Coming Back
1.plot: After an upsetting 6th place finish for The California All Stars SMOED at the Cheerleading World Championship, it's time for Eddie Rios to assemble the troops and head into battle.

2.title: 2 out of 4
2.plot: It's Day 2 of cheerleading tryouts for the Cali Smoed and the competition is strong...or is it? It takes a certain type of athlete to earn a coveted spot as a boy on this team.

3.title: Work For Your Spot!
3.plot: It's the first practice of the season and coach Eddie takes no time at all in making it clear that no one's spot is secure. Mathiue is back from Canada with the hopes of reliving his dream. Meanwhile, returner Tawnie is hoping to earn a permanent spot on the team and finish out the season.

4.title: Cali Camp 2016 Pt.1
4.plot: It's time for Cali Super Camp 2016. Everyone knows that dropping stunts at camp is not okay. Newcomer Peyton has had a taste of success on her old team.

5.title: Cali Camp 2016 Part 2
5.plot: The new team is put to the test during show offs. Will they be able to follow Eddie's most important rule of cheer camp? Later, the kids get loose and show what they've got at the Cali Camp Talent Show.

6.title: Cali Camp 2016 Part 3
6.plot: Another day, another Show Off. New flyer Malieya is put to the test as Cali Smoed teams up with Cali Snipers for pyramids.

8.title: The Hunger Games
8.plot: Flight School is in session here at the California All Stars Camarillo. With seven flyers up for five coveted spots it's time to narrow down the pack.

9.title: Do or Die
9.plot: Accidents happen and an unfortunate event might just spell the end of the season for one of the veteran athletes. Meanwhile newcomer Sharee has come in to try her luck as a member of the team.

10.title: Making the Cut
10.plot: It looks like it might be out with the new and in with the old. Veteran flyer Maia makes a comeback in a new way. Meanwhile, rookie Sharee is realizing that she may have bit off more than she can chew.

11.title: Goodbye Payton
11.plot: Summer's over and the roster changes result in the loss of a veteran team member. Goodbyes are always hard but a special birthday surprise keeps everyone in high spirits. The team is still missing two boys and with choreography fast approaching the team is starting to feel the pressure.

12.title: That's My Boy!
12.plot: After the long awaited search, SMOED may have found their final boy. This leaves alternate Alex to fend for his spot as the curse of the 4th boy looms near.

13.title: Let's Get Reckless
13.plot: California All Stars level six team is Reckless and they're getting ready for competition season. Michaeleddie is back and ready to help take the team to first place but first Orby needs to pick the final team members. It all comes down to who will hit and who will miss and the pressure is high for these two flyers.

14.title: Cali Style!
14.plot: Choreographer Robbii Sedillo is here to let SMOED know just what Cali Style is all about.

15.title: Toughen Up
15.plot: A few of the girls head over to the WOW Wrestling match to find out just what it takes to get tough. Back at the gym, a few of the newbies find out that if they want to make it on this team they are going to have to get even tougher.

16.title: Crossing Over
16.plot: It's the final practice before the season opening showcase and both Cali Smoed and Reckless have a lot to prove.

17.title: Push!
17.plot: Showcase is finally here. Not everything is going as planned. Especially when major changes happen at the last minute.

18.title: Everything Counts!
18.plot: With the first competition of the season just one week away, the team isn't sure what they are going to do to replace veteran Madi. Team morale looks to be taking a hit but Eddie is sure to remind Cali SMOED that everything counts.

19.title: Holiday Special
19.plot: The California All Stars head down to the Salvation Army Youth Center to give back to the community at the annual Toy n Joy Christmas event.

20.title: Slay Another Day
20.plot: Love is in the air as Sierra's first boyfriend comes to support the team at their first competition. Will nerves set in for the newbies as Cali SMOED hits the floor?

21.title: We Can't Get Hurt!
21.plot: Mattieu's celebrates his 19th birthday with his cheer family since his real family is so far away. While Madi and Maia are overcoming their injuries it looks like another member might just be out for the count.

23.title: The Walking Dead
23.plot: It's hell week for SMOED and Reckless. That means injuries and illness--A.K.A the plague; but it's also bid week. Both teams must figure out if they can pull through by the weekend, and find a way to compete for a full-paid bid to Worlds.

25.title: We Have To Hit!
25.plot: It's day 2 of GSSA and Reckless is feeling confident, but are they going to be a Day 1 team? Meanwhile SMOED is under pressure after their not so perfect day 1 showing. SMOED must now redeem themselves and hit their routine, or Worlds may be out of the picture this year.

26.title: The Comeback Kid
26.plot: It's the first day back from GSSA and the team looks a little different. Diego has to fill in, and the team gets a new addition-or an old one. Eddie has one month to get the team performance-ready, but someone is struggling more than others.

27.title: Part of the Puzzle
27.plot: Eddie brings in a special guest to help with the cali smoed look. The girls get back to tumbling after facing numerous injuries, while the boys work on their coed stunts-some struggling more than others. Later the team drills elites, but it seems nothing is going well.

28.title: Kassidy is Back!
28.plot: It looks like a long time veteran of the California All Stars might be making a comeback. Meanwhile, someones second chance at a dream might be taken away.

29.title: Drop it Like it's Hot
29.plot: After Palm Springs, Nfinity Legend Santon McCray comes to whip the boys into shape. Meanwhile, it's time to get into gear for NCA, but one member is a bit homesick.

30.title: You Can't Win!
30.plot: It's the last practice before The NCA National Championships and Eddie is at his wits end. Will the team show that they have what it takes to take back that top spot!?

31.title: Blast from the Past
31.plot: The team is back from a 4th place finish at NCA All Stars and Eddie decides it's time to make some changes. Unfortunately that means that someones spot just might be in jeopardy.

32.title: No Time For Games
32.plot: With only one competition left for Reckless to get the full paid bid there is absolutely no time for games. Orby is making some roster changes and no ones spot is safe.

33.title: Crushed Dreams
33.plot: It's official, SMOED is going to Hawaii. But is it Aloha for newcomer Ally and goodbye for two members who have already been given a second chance? Someones dreams just might be crushed.

34.title: A Little Shook
34.plot: When a Cali SMOED flyer gets a very unexpected injury it's all hands on deck to try and find a replacement. But what happens when Coach Eddie realizes they may simply be out of options?

35.title: You Look A Mess
35.plot: It's the last practice before Hawaii and Coach Eddie and Orby have made their pick for a replacement flyer.

36.title: Aloha SMOED
36.plot: Cali SMOED is off to Hawaii. With 20 kids on one plane there is bound to be a few adventures. The team heads to Jade's home gym, Island Elite, to brush up on a few skills, but it seems like an old injury may be haunting Sierra.

37.title: Big Girls Don't Cry
37.plot: The competition is just one day away and it seems as if things are going in one ear and out the other. Hopefully a luau bonding night will get the team come back together.

38.title: April Fools
38.plot: Cali SMOED is ready to hit the mat at the Aloha Championships in Hawaii. But first, the team gets to have a little fun in the sun.

39.title: No Fun in the Sun
39.plot: The team is feeling great after hitting zero on Day 1 at the Aloha Championships but one member of the team isn't feeling so great after all.

40.title: The Last Pass
40.plot: Cali SMOED has one last chance to put in some work at the gym before heading off to the USASF World Cheerleading Championships. Madi, Jazzy and Sierra are coming to terms with having to leave the gym where they grew up.

41.title: Finish Strong
41.plot: Are you ready to see two full performances? These athletes will perform one last time in the Cali gym, before they head off to Orlando.

42.title: Off to Worlds We Go!
42.plot: It's off to Worlds 2017 for Cali SMOED. Malieya has never competed on in the Fieldhouse and hopes that her veteran teammates can give her a few words of advice.

43.title: Today Is Not the Day
43.plot: It's the day before Worlds, Cali Smoed is having a rough practice at Top Gun and coach Eddie is NOT having it. Later, the seniors get together to reminisce about their time as part of the Smamily.

44.title: Worlds 2017 Day 1
44.plot: It's Day 1 of The USASF World Cheerleading Championships and the pressure is on to hit.

45.title: Worlds 2017 Day 2
45.plot: After a successful first day of Semi Finals at the USASF World Cheerleading Championships, it all comes down to this.

46.title: End of an Era
46.plot: All great things must come to end. The 2016-2017 seniors of Cali Smoed are moving on and it's time to say goodbye to long time veteran Madi Corsello.

-1.title: Don't Be A Psycho!
-1.plot: It's Day 1 of GSSA, and Reckless and SMOED are both competing for paid bids to Worlds. Reckless has been struggling all week with their stunts, and warm-ups are proving no better. Meanwhile, SMOED looks as if they may have pulled together after their week of hell. Though when it comes to competitions, nothing ever goes as planned.

imdb.plot outline: Cheerleaders takes viewers inside the world of the 2012 World Champion cheerleading squad, The California All Stars SMOED. The series follows the team inside and outside the cheer gym during competition season as they laugh, cry, celebrate and breakdown dealing with the stress and pressure required to maintain their championship title.
